Heat a wok or large skillet with oil on medium heat. Place carrots, onions, green beans, green peas, broccoli, green peppers and red peppers. Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes. Make a well in the center of vegetables. Place ham in and stir to moisten. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. In a small, lightly greased skillet, scramble the eggs until firm. Cut eggs up into small pieces. Stir vegetables, ham and eggs together. Mix the soy sauce, water and cornstarch in a bowl and pour into center of wok or skillet. Stir quickly until it begins to thicken.